summaries.title: Summary 313.1
summaries.summaryText: Participation in SHPE and campus cultural centers provided Maria a sense of belonging and identity affirmation. These communities offered emotional support and mentorship that she could not easily find in her department. [Part 4/4]

summaries.title: Summary 313.2
summaries.summaryText: Daniel expressed pride in representing his family’s aspirations but also noted ongoing struggles with imposter syndrome. He values belonging through peer groups that normalize his experiences as a first-gen student of color in STEM. [Part 3/4]

timelinePoints.eventDescription: Joined the Engineering Learning Community, finding peer mentors and emotional support. [Timeline 2]
Presented research poster at a regional engineering conference, receiving recognition from faculty mentors. [Timeline 1]
Presented senior capstone project on sustainable urban drainage systems, earning department recognition. [Timeline 4]
Joined the Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers during her first semester to find community and mentorship. [Timeline 1]

themes.title: Normalizing Mental Health Conversations in STEM
themes.description: Sarah’s work highlights the growing student-led shift toward wellness advocacy within rigorous majors. [Extended 2]

themes.title: Mentorship Networks as Retention Mechanisms
themes.description: Mentorship emerges as a consistent strategy for increasing belonging and persistence for students from marginalized groups. Aaliyah’s mentorship program demonstrates how peer-led initiatives can fill institutional gaps. [Extended 1]

themes.title: Sense of Belonging in STEM for Students of Color
themes.description: Maria’s reflections highlight how peer representation and visibility in classrooms significantly influence belonging and persistence for Latina women in engineering. [Extended 4]

quotes.quoteText: If I can use my position to make sure everyone gets a fair shot in our projects, that’s what good leadership looks like. [Context 3]
Sometimes I look around my class and I’m the only Latina — it makes me question whether I belong here. [Context 4]
Mentorship is how we survive here — sharing what we’ve learned keeps us going when the system doesn’t always see us. [Context 1]
I love leading projects, but it’s exhausting always being the one to explain why diversity matters in engineering teams. [Context 2]

areasForImprovement.title: Enhance First-Gen Orientation Programs
areasForImprovement.description: Provide stronger academic transition support for first-generation students entering engineering. [Extended 1]

areasForImprovement.title: Expand Visibility of First-Gen Student Resources
areasForImprovement.description: Current communication about financial aid, academic advising, and mentorship resources does not adequately reach first-generation students. Improving targeted outreach through orientation and department emails could reduce inequities in access to support. [Extended 1]
